[2] Timor-Leste, domestic pigs, FAO
Date: Thu 3 Oct 2019
Source: FAO/EMPRES -- Animal Health: ASF Asia weekly update for 3 Oct 2019 [abridged, edited]
http://www.fao.org/ag/againfo/programmes/en/empres/ASF/Situation_update.html


Timor-Leste: The Ministry of Agriculture and Fisheries announced the confirmation of ASF outbreak on [27 Sep 2019] as hundreds of pigs have died because of the disease in the country; samples sent to Australia confirmed that these animals suffered from African swine fever [see press release at http://timor-leste.gov.tl/?p=23034&lang=en].

The disease started on [9 Sep 2019]; a total of 100 outbreaks in smallholder pig farms [have] been recorded in the Capital City, Dili. The Veterinary Directorate reported on OIE WAHIS that there were unconfirmed reports of pig deaths in other towns on the same coast side of the country, in Baucau and Liquica municipalities [OIE immediate notification, with map, dated 27 Sep 2019, at
https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=31960].

