[The recent long-range leap of ASF to the territories of the Philippines and Timor-Leste (East Timor) is visualized in the OIE interactive map at https://tinyurl.com/y4flfd5s (click on the SE Asia cluster to center, zoom in). Timor-Leste is situated about 2700 km (1678 mi) from the infected region in the Philippines, and more than 3000 km (1864 mi) from southern Viet Nam, which are the closest territories known to be ASF-infected.

Other countries in this part of the world are at immediate risk, including Indonesia, Malaysia and New Guinea. The grave concern of Australia has been addressed in 20191001.6702803.

The source and route of these introductions are yet to be clarified. - Mod.AS

